<subsection xml:id="subsec-congruence-in-triangles" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Congruence in Triangles</title>
    <objectives component="outcomes">
        <introduction xml:id="auto_k6ln8hle">
            <dl>
                <li xml:id="auto_aw7iethy">
                    <title>Strand</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_myhxsvbw">
                        2.0 Measurements and Geometry
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_8oxx8xbw">
                    <title>Sub-Strand</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_x3urb1fy">
                        2.2 Reflection and Congruence
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_undsl2mt">
                    <title>Specific Learning Outcomes</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_e4kqh88a">
                        Carry out congruence tests for triangles
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_9o7u61zm" component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Grade Level</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_n6sorqh3">
                        10
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_q24tqd7x" component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Estimated Duration</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_av065htm">
                        40 minutes
                    </p>
                </li>
            </dl>
            <p xml:id="auto_iihyl9e0" component="lesson-plan">
                <p xml:id="auto_1dyg68qh"> Upon completion of this lesson, learners will be able to:
                <ol>
                    <li xml:id="auto_0rysnyb3">
                        <p xml:id="auto_mky3spwy">
                            <alert>Know (Conceptual Understanding):</alert> Define congruent triangles as triangles with the same shape, size, and all corresponding sides and angles equal. Identify the five congruence tests: SSS, SAS, ASA, RHS, and AAS. State the minimum conditions to prove congruence.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_b3pw04km">
                        <p xml:id="auto_m8y5l4fo">
                            <alert>Do (Procedural Skill):</alert> Apply congruence tests (SSS, SAS, ASA, RHS, AAS) to determine whether two triangles are congruent. Use ruler and protractor to construct and compare triangles. Write congruence statements with correct vertex correspondence.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_oa0s2qr6">
                        <p xml:id="auto_akxxr4o1">
                            <alert>Apply (Application/Problem-Solving):</alert> Solve problems involving congruent triangles in real-world contexts. Apply congruence tests to prove geometric properties. Use congruence to verify structural integrity and symmetry.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
                </p>
            </p>
        </introduction>
    </objectives>
    <axiom component="resources">
        <!-- Link to blurb -->
        <xi:include href="../../resources-blurb-lesson.ptx" />

        <sbsgroup widths="45% 45%" margins="2% 2%">
            <sidebyside>
                <p xml:id="auto_ipha0ole">
                    <dataurl source="lesson_plans/measurements-and-geometry/reflection-and-congruence/congruence-in-triangles.pdf"> Lesson Plan </dataurl>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_v9wnfc4q">
                    <dataurl source="lesson_plans/measurements-and-geometry/reflection-and-congruence/step-by-step-guide_congruence-in-triangles.pdf"> Step-by-Step Guide </dataurl>
                </p>
            </sidebyside>
        </sbsgroup>
    </axiom>
    <xi:include href="../../resources-materials.ptx" />

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Problem-Solving and Discovery</title>
        <dl>
            <li xml:id="auto_spaa9xap">
                <title>Suggested Time</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_mw80jg7l">
                    15 minutes
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_rckmhltz">
                <title>Objective</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_2lgoykjd">
                    Cut-Out Triangle Matching <mdash/> learners discover what minimum measurements make two triangles congruent.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_rwrr2dh0">
                <title>Grouping</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_qzzbe4uq">
                    Groups
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_u4jg6wsd">
                <title>Materials</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_ygxfwcxs">
                    Rulers, protractors, scissors, card stock
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_nirl8mx3">
                <title>Teacher's Role</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_hmchzeb8">
                    Ask probing questions: <q>What measurements make triangles identical?</q>, <q>Is knowing all angles enough?</q>, <q>What about three sides?</q>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_j8rc4d0b">
                <title>Expected Discovery</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_rtnoasup">
                    Same 3 sides, or 2 sides + included angle, or 2 angles + included side <m>\rightarrow</m> congruent.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_xp637icc">
                <title>Interactive Exploration</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_xd1xxdbn">
                    If you have an Internet connection, get Learners to try the interactive exploration.
                </p>
            </li>
        </dl>
    </axiom>

    <activity xml:id="auto_02na0013">
    <statement>
      <p xml:id="auto_ej27xeef">
        <term>Work in groups</term>
      </p>
      <p xml:id="auto_va3xowu8">
        Conditions for Congruence in Triangles 
      </p>
      <p xml:id="auto_90w1k0pq">
        <term>Materials</term>
      </p>
      <p xml:id="auto_fx1wbn3k">
        <ul xml:id="auto_ge9wofyc">
