    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Differentiation</title>

        <table xml:id="auto_3xf66yk5">
            <title>Differentiation</title>
            <tabular halign="left">
                <row header="yes" bottom="minor">
                    <cell>Learner Group</cell>
                    <cell>Strategy &amp; Learning Experience</cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Struggling Learners (Support)</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <line><alert>Scaffolding:</alert> Provide physical cut-outs for matching. Use colour-coded sides and angles. Start with SSS only. Provide a flowchart for choosing the correct test. Pair with a mentor learner.</line>
                    </cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>On-Level Learners (Core)</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <line>The core lesson activities as described above. Learners work through all five tests, complete coordinate geometry problems, and write formal congruence proofs.</line>
                    </cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Advanced Learners (Challenge)</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <line><alert>Extended Learning Experience:</alert> 1) Prove that the diagonals of a rhombus bisect each other using congruent triangles. 2) Prove that the diagonals of a rectangle are equal using congruent triangles. 3) Investigate why SSA fails by constructing a counterexample.</line>
                    </cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>
        </table>
    </axiom>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Extension Activities</title>
        <paragraphs>
            <title>1. Prove Rhombus Diagonals Bisect Each Other</title>
            <p xml:id="auto_41gib8og">
                <m>ABCD</m> is a rhombus. Diagonals <m>AC</m> and <m>BD</m> meet at <m>O</m>.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_47c9xxya">
                In <m>\triangle ABD</m> and <m>\triangle CBD</m>: <m>AB = CB</m> (sides of rhombus), <m>BD = BD</m> (common), <m>AD = CD</m> (sides of rhombus) <m>\Rightarrow</m> SSS <m>\Rightarrow \triangle ABD \cong \triangle CBD</m>.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_zgbnnclr">
                Therefore <m>\angle ABD = \angle CBD</m>, so <m>BO</m> bisects <m>\angle B</m>.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_o8han4w8">
                Then in <m>\triangle ABO</m> and <m>\triangle CBO</m>: <m>AB = CB</m>, <m>\angle ABD = \angle CBD</m>, <m>BO = BO</m> <m>\Rightarrow</m> SAS <m>\Rightarrow \triangle ABO \cong \triangle CBO</m>.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_7h5pzphv">
                Therefore <m>AO = CO</m> and <m>\angle AOB = \angle COB = 90°</m>. The diagonals bisect each other at right angles.
            </p>
        </paragraphs>
        <paragraphs>
            <title>2. Prove Rectangle Diagonals Are Equal</title>
            <p xml:id="auto_6rury1hd">
                <m>ABCD</m> is a rectangle. Consider <m>\triangle ABC</m> and <m>\triangle DCB</m>.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_06om1nis">
                <m>AB = DC</m> (opposite sides of rectangle), <m>BC = BC</m> (common), <m>\angle ABC = \angle DCB = 90°</m> <m>\Rightarrow</m> SAS <m>\Rightarrow \triangle ABC \cong \triangle DCB</m>.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_c196vm7c">
                Therefore <m>AC = DB</m>. The diagonals are equal.
            </p>
        </paragraphs>
        <paragraphs>
            <title>3. SSA Counterexample</title>
            <p xml:id="auto_vd7cbi3l">
                Given <m>AB = 5</m>, <m>BC = 3</m>, <m>\angle A = 30°</m>. Two possible triangles can be constructed (the ambiguous case). This is why SSA is not a valid congruence test.
            </p>
        </paragraphs>
    </axiom>
    <xi:include href="../../resources-assessment.ptx" />
    <xi:include href="../../resources-reflection.ptx"/>
</subsection>